      <note>Lingua is used to detect the language of documents, supporting 75 languages.

In this sample, six identical HTML documents (with broken tags) are analysed, with the content in: English, French, Spanish, Korean, Marathi, and Hindi.

When preprocess=false, the detection fails to correctly identify French, mistaking it for English (with high confidence). 
This demonstrates that while Lingua performs well even with HTML, it emphasises the importance of
 pre-processing (i.e. cleaning) documents before language detection.

Reference:
https://github.com/pemistahl/lingua</note>
